article.headline: S&P 500 breaks to less-charted territory, rallies to tag next resistance
article.body: U.S. stocks are higher early Thursday, rising to extend a jagged but persistent October rally attempt. Against this backdrop, the S&P 500 has reached a less-charted patch at one-month highs, rising to tag next resistance (3,444). Before detailing the U.S. markets’ wider view, the S&P 500’s hourly chart highlights the past two weeks. ...
